Bandits have attacked villages in Mashegu and Kontagora local government Niger State, killing two persons and abducted five others. According to reports, the bandits stormed five villages on Friday in large numbers, operated for hours and rustled several cattle as the villagers fled their homes for safety. It was also gathered that the bandits after a few hours, called families of victims to demand ransom. Leaders’ Honesty Will Check Security Challenges – Bishop Eichie IPOB Allays Fears Of Lockdown In South-East, Announces… Meanwhile, the Niger state police command is yet to confirm the incident.